<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,618,2011]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,726,751]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[330,500,726,750]" class="Insecta" family="Drilidae" genus="Drilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nemethi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[330,500,726,750]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">Drilus nemethi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[509,601,726,751]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[509,601,726,751]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from similarly colored 
<taxonomicName box="[958,1063,727,750]" class="Insecta" family="Drilidae" genus="Drilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectus">
<emphasis box="[958,978,727,750]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[995,1063,727,750]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">rectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by considerably larger eyes, the head including eyes wider than anterior pronotal margin (
<figureCitation box="[801,904,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[170,1419,200,1853]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[156,1430,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. General appearance. 1 — Drilus adustus; 2 — D. akbesianus; 3 — D. bicolor; 4 — D. nemethi sp. nov.; 5 — D. rectus; 6 — D. rufipes. Scale 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226484/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">
Figs 
<number box="[859,904,762,787]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5</number>
</figureCitation>
), slender antennae (
<figureCitation box="[1129,1259,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1576,1599]" captionTargetBox="[154,1423,199,1547]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1555]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 18. Antenna. 7 — Drilus adustus; 8 — D. akbesianus; 9 — D. bicolor; 10 — D. nemethi sp. nov.; 11 — D. rectus; 12 — D. rufipes. Pronotum. 13 — Drilus adustus; 14 — D. akbesianus; 15 — D. bicolor; 16 — D. nemethi sp. nov.; 17 — D. rectus; 18 — D. rufipes. Scale 1.0 mm (Figs 7 – 12), 0.5 mm (Figs 13 – 18)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226485/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">
Figs 
<number box="[1187,1259,763,787]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" value="10.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="10.0">10–11</number>
</figureCitation>
), antennomeres 
<number box="[151,192,799,823]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
only slightly lighter than remaining ones, uniform coloration of ventral parts, and rounded apical part of paramerae (
<figureCitation box="[286,422,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1605,1628]" captionTargetBox="[162,1421,342,1577]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,337,1584]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 24. Male genitalia. 19 — Drilus adustus; 20 — D. akbesianus; 21 — D. bicolor; 22 — D. nemethi sp. nov.; 23 — D. rectus; 24 — D. rufipes. Scale 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226486/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">
Figs 
<number box="[347,422,835,859]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" value="22.5" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="22.0">22–23</number>
</figureCitation>
). The differences between 
<taxonomicName box="[739,867,835,859]" class="Insecta" family="Drilidae" genus="Drilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nemethi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[739,759,835,858]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[778,867,835,859]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">nemethi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[877,971,834,859]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[877,971,834,859]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1034,1197,835,859]" class="Insecta" family="Drilidae" genus="Drilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="akbesianus">
<emphasis box="[1034,1054,835,858]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1072,1197,835,859]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">akbesianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are given under the diagnosis of the latter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="464" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,618,2011]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,906,931]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Body medium-sized, elongate, 
<number box="[799,884,906,931]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" value="3.4000000000000004" valueMax="3.6" valueMin="3.2">3.2–3.6</number>
times as long as width at humeri, moderately convex dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[350,423,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[170,1419,200,1853]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[156,1430,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. General appearance. 1 — Drilus adustus; 2 — D. akbesianus; 3 — D. bicolor; 4 — D. nemethi sp. nov.; 5 — D. rectus; 6 — D. rufipes. Scale 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226484/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">
Fig. 
<number box="[406,423,943,967]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Head, elytra and metaventrite dark brown to black, antennae brown, other body parts including elytral sutura light brown; entire body covered with yellow pubescence.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,618,2011]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">
Head slightly hypognathous, including eyes apparently wider than anterior margin of pronotum. Surface of cranium sparsely, moderately deeply punctured, slightly wrinkled, with moderately deep and wide depression between conspicuous antennal sockets, dorsally with sparse semierect pubescence; clypeal margin widely concave. Eyes large, hemispherically prominent, their frontal distance 
<number box="[844,928,1122,1147]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" value="1.7000000000000002" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.6">1.6–1.8</number>
times eye diameter. Mandibles long, falcate, considerably curved, shiny; incisor margin with conspicuous tooth in middle part. Maxillary palpi slender, apical palpomere slightly compressed and obliquely cut; labial palpi tiny, apical palpomere pointed. Antennae 
<number box="[1400,1427,1195,1219]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" value="11.0">11</number>
- segmented, reaching third of elytral length, scapus long, robust, pedicel short, small, antennomere 
<number box="[1325,1339,1231,1255]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" value="3.0">3</number>
slightly serrate, more than 
<number box="[366,380,1267,1291]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" value="3.0">3</number>
times longer than antennomere 
<number box="[751,767,1267,1291]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" value="2.0">2</number>
, antennomeres 
<number box="[946,1003,1267,1291]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" value="7.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="4.0">4–10</number>
shortly flabellate, subequal in length, with flattened lamellae, apical antennomere longest, more than twice longer than stem of penultimate antennomere (
<figureCitation box="[159,243,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1576,1599]" captionTargetBox="[154,1423,199,1547]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1555]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 18. Antenna. 7 — Drilus adustus; 8 — D. akbesianus; 9 — D. bicolor; 10 — D. nemethi sp. nov.; 11 — D. rectus; 12 — D. rufipes. Pronotum. 13 — Drilus adustus; 14 — D. akbesianus; 15 — D. bicolor; 16 — D. nemethi sp. nov.; 17 — D. rectus; 18 — D. rufipes. Scale 1.0 mm (Figs 7 – 12), 0.5 mm (Figs 13 – 18)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226485/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,243,1339,1363]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,618,2011]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">
Pronotum flat, widest at middle part, 
<number box="[626,710,1375,1399]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" value="1.35" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.3">1.3–1.4</number>
times wider posteriorly than length at midline. Anterior margin straight or almost straight, lateral margins slightly convex, posterior margin considerably convex, sinuate in middle. Anterior angles almost rectangular, posterior angles prominent (
<figureCitation box="[1027,1119,1446,1471]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 18" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1576,1599]" captionTargetBox="[154,1423,199,1547]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1555]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 18. Antenna. 7 — Drilus adustus; 8 — D. akbesianus; 9 — D. bicolor; 10 — D. nemethi sp. nov.; 11 — D. rectus; 12 — D. rufipes. Pronotum. 13 — Drilus adustus; 14 — D. akbesianus; 15 — D. bicolor; 16 — D. nemethi sp. nov.; 17 — D. rectus; 18 — D. rufipes. Scale 1.0 mm (Figs 7 – 12), 0.5 mm (Figs 13 – 18)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226485/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">
Fig. 
<number box="[1088,1119,1446,1471]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
); surface of disc sparsely punctured, with sparse, semierect, long setae. Scutellum flat, triangle-shaped, widely rounded apically. Prosternum transverse, prosternal process short, slightly elevated in middle part. Mesoventrite v-shaped, with frontal margin depressed medially. Metaventrite large, trapezoidal, sparsely punctured. Elytra subparallel-sided, widest at humeri, 
<number box="[151,235,1591,1615]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" value="2.55" valueMax="2.7" valueMin="2.4">2.4–2.7</number>
times longer than width at humeri, tapered apically, wrinkled. Each elytron with longitudinal keel running from humeral part to apex, inconspicuous in apical half, with semierect pubescence. Abdomen slender, either short or considerably long, with several apical sternites surpassing elytra, ventrites with moderately deep punctures and sparse, long setae. Legs slender, slightly compressed, with sparse, long, semierect setae, coxae long, robust, trochanters slender, obliquely attached to femora, tarsomeres 
<number box="[850,892,1735,1759]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
subequal in length, tarsomere 
<number box="[1244,1258,1735,1759]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" value="4.0">4</number>
shortest, apical tarsomere long, claws simple, slender, slightly curved.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,618,2011]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">
Male genitalia with curved phallus; short paramerae with inner margin forming conspicuous fold, with setae in apical part; phallobase robust, wide, longer than paramerae (
<figureCitation box="[828,912,1842,1867]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 24" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1605,1628]" captionTargetBox="[162,1421,342,1577]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,337,1584]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 24. Male genitalia. 19 — Drilus adustus; 20 — D. akbesianus; 21 — D. bicolor; 22 — D. nemethi sp. nov.; 23 — D. rectus; 24 — D. rufipes. Scale 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226486/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">
Fig. 
<number box="[880,912,1843,1867]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,618,2011]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464">
Measurements. BL 
<quantity box="[423,562,1878,1903]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.55" metricValueMax="9.3" metricValueMin="5.8" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" unit="mm" value="7.55" valueMax="9.3" valueMin="5.8">5.8–9.3 mm</quantity>
, EL 
<number box="[619,653,1879,1903]" pageId="7" pageNumber="464" value="4.3">4.3</number>
–7.0 mm, WH 
